snippet.textDisplay: Someone might have mentioned this already, but I have an idea for dipping the cupcakes so they don't get soggy. Arrange the frosting on parchment paper first, freeze it, and put the frozen frosting on a cake pop stick for dipping. Then, when the oil has dried (but before the frosting thaws), move it on top of the cupcake.
snippet.textOriginal: Someone might have mentioned this already, but I have an idea for dipping the cupcakes so they don't get soggy. Arrange the frosting on parchment paper first, freeze it, and put the frozen frosting on a cake pop stick for dipping. Then, when the oil has dried (but before the frosting thaws), move it on top of the cupcake.
